30/11/2008
ATHENS, Greece -- Police announced on Friday (November 28th) they have smashed a network trafficking illegal immigrants from Asia to Greece via Turkey. Three members of the gang have been arrested. Police traced the network after the bodies of two immigrants were found on Paros Island, south of Athens, on Tuesday. Investigators determined the victims were part of a group of 32 illegal immigrants from Pakistan and Bangladesh who were being kept in a refrigerated truck, owned by a 43-year-old resident of Athens.
In other news, a Greek ship seized by Somali pirates over two months ago was released on Friday along with its 25-member crew. No one aboard the vessel, sailing under a Maltese flag, was harmed. All the crew members were from the Philippines. (Kathimerini - 29/11/08; AP - 28/11/08)
